      "writtenOn": "2020-12-21T15:59:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm. I don\u0027t think I understand the semantics of store128?\n\nWith the striped output, the program looks like:\n\n6 registers, 15 instructions:\n0\tr0 \u003d splat 3F800000 (1)\n1\tr1 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 24\n2\tr2 \u003d splat 3B808081 (0.0039215689)\n3\tr3 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 8\n4\tr4 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 0\n5\tr3 \u003d add_f32 r4 r3\n6\tr3 \u003d mul_f32 r3 r2\n7\tr4 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 4\nloop:\n8\t    store32 arg(3) r0\n9\t    store32 arg(2) r1\n10\t    store32 arg(1) r3\n11\t    r5 \u003d index\n12\t    r5 \u003d add_f32 r5 r4\n13\t    r5 \u003d mul_f32 r5 r2\n14\t    store32 arg(0) r5\n\n\n... changing it to RGBA_F32, it turns into:\n\n6 registers, 13 instructions:\n0\tr0 \u003d splat 3F800000 (1)\n1\tr1 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 24\n2\tr2 \u003d splat 3B808081 (0.0039215689)\n3\tr3 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 8\n4\tr4 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 0\n5\tr3 \u003d add_f32 r4 r3\n6\tr3 \u003d mul_f32 r3 r2\n7\tr4 \u003d uniform32 arg(0) 4\nloop:\n8\t    store128 arg(0) r1 r0 1\n9\t    r5 \u003d index\n10\t    r5 \u003d add_f32 r5 r4\n11\t    r5 \u003d mul_f32 r5 r2\n12\t    store128 arg(0) r5 r3 0\n\nThat\u0027s got *two* 128-bit stores per iteration? (And ops only have three args, so I don\u0027t quite get the breakdown).",
      "parentUuid": "604aa2a8_2ebd9603",
      "revId": "a89ade1dde2feac9473bd5eb1dc0e234156c15a8",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
